<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF9BFFB5C9F5FC17FAADB0A6" blockId="14.[136,1452,839,1395]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C9F5FC17FE0EB78A" bold="true" box="[189,432,980,1006]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5C8E7FC17FDC6B78A" authorityName="Muller Argoviensis" authorityYear="1874" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[431,632,980,1006]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setosa">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C8E7FC17FDC6B78A" box="[431,632,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Euphorbia setosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be easily identified among the species in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF9BFFB5CC7EFC17FA15B78A" box="[1334,1451,980,1006]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
by its cyathial glands with erect and pubescent petaloid appendages, while others species’ petaloid appendages are always patent and glabrate. By having cyathia arranged in capitate dichasia and hirsute stems, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CDE7FBD9FACAB050" authorityName="Muller Argoviensis" authorityYear="1874" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[1199,1396,1050,1076]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setosa">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CDE7FBD9FACAB050" box="[1199,1396,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Euphorbia setosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5C825FBFDFE7BB03C" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[365,453,1086,1112]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C825FBFDFE7BB03C" box="[365,453,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5C8B9FBFDFD1EB03C" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[497,672,1086,1112]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C8B9FBFDFD1EB03C" box="[497,672,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but these species may be distinguished by their lanceolate blades, cladodromous venation, entire leaf margin (
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CB3CFBA1FD2CB01F" box="[628,658,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">vs.</emphasis>
elliptic blades, actinodromous venation, serrate leaf margin in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CC1EFBA1FA15B01F" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1366,1451,1121,1147]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CC1EFBA1FA15B01F" box="[1366,1451,1121,1147]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5C9F3FB46FED7B0FA" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[187,361,1156,1182]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C9F3FB46FED7B0FA" box="[187,361,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), number of flowers in each staminate cymule (
<quantity id="4CFCFFCBFF9BFFB5CAD4FB47FBBDB0FA" box="[924,1027,1156,1182]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" metricValueMax="3.048" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" unit="in" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12 in</quantity>
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CD45FB46FB21B0FA" box="[1037,1183,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CD45FB46FBC8B0FA" authorityName="Muller Argoviensis" authorityYear="1874" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[1037,1142,1157,1182]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setosa">E. setosa</taxonomicName>
vs.
</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CFCFFCBFF9BFFB5CDE1FB47FB4DB0FA" box="[1193,1267,1156,1182]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.81" metricValueMax="5.08" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" unit="in" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CDB5FB46FAE8B0FA" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1277,1366,1156,1182]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CDB5FB46FAE8B0FA" box="[1277,1366,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CCDBFB46FEAAB0A5" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CCDBFB46FEAAB0A5" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and alveolate seeds coat (
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CB01FB6BFDD6B0A5" box="[585,616,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">vs.</emphasis>
seeds with transverse ridges in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CA84FB6BFB9FB0A5" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[972,1057,1191,1217]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CA84FB6BFB9FB0A5" box="[972,1057,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CD10FB6BFABDB0A5" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[1112,1283,1191,1217]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CD10FB6BFABDB0A5" box="[1112,1283,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF9BFFB5C9C0FB09FD6BB116" blockId="14.[136,1452,839,1395]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">
The species is commonly misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CB28FB09FCA5B080" box="[608,795,1226,1252]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloi">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CB28FB09FCA5B080" box="[608,795,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Euphorbia selloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Klotzsch &amp; Garcke in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF952FDFFF9BFFB5CD6CFB09FB4FB081" author="Klotzsch, J. F." box="[1060,1265,1226,1253]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref10883" refString="Klotzsch, J. F. (1860) Linne's naturlich Pflanzenklasse Tricoccae des Berliner Herbarium's im Allgemeinen und die naturliche Ordnung Euphorbiaceae insbesondere. Abhandlungen der Koniglichen Akademie der Wissenschaften in Berlin 1859: 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1860">Klotzsch 1860: 32</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EF952FDFFF9BFFB5CC48FB09FF11B16C" author="Boissier, E." pageId="14" pageNumber="207" pagination="3 - 188" refId="ref9728" refString="Boissier, E. (1862) Euphorbieae. In: Candolle, A. L. P. P. de (Ed.) Prodromus Systematics Universalis Regni Vegetabilis 15 (2). Victor Masson, Paris, pp. 3 - 188." type="book chapter" year="1862">Boissier (1862: 50)</bibRefCitation>
, which is in fact very similar to it. However, it can be distinguished from it by its cyathial glands with erect and pubescent petaloid appendages (
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C8A7FAD1FDB0B14F" box="[495,526,1298,1323]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">vs.</emphasis>
patent and glabrous in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CA45FAD1FCD6B14F" box="[781,872,1297,1323]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloi">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CA45FAD1FCD6B14F" box="[781,872,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. selloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Besides this, the geographic distribution is distinct between both species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5C8CCFAF6FE57B12A" authorityName="Muller Argoviensis" authorityYear="1874" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[388,489,1333,1358]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setosa">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C8CCFAF6FE57B12A" box="[388,489,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. setosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in central–southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F31312BEFF9BFFB5CA02FAF7FC30B12A" box="[842,910,1332,1358]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CA8CFAF6FB9EB12A" box="[964,1056,1332,1358]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloi">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CA8CFAF6FB9EB12A" box="[964,1056,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">E. selloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in southern 
<collectingCountry id="F31312BEFF9BFFB5CDB2FAF7FAFFB12A" box="[1274,1345,1332,1358]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry id="F31312BEFF9BFFB5C9C0FA9BFF49B116" box="[136,247,1368,1394]" name="Argentina" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F31312BEFF9BFFB5C866FA9AFE2EB117" box="[302,400,1369,1395]" name="Uruguay" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF952FDFFF9BFFB5C8D6FA9BFD76B116" author="Simmons, M. P. &amp; Hayden, W. J." box="[414,712,1368,1394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" pagination="155 - 180" refId="ref11773" refString="Simmons, M. P. &amp; Hayden, W. J. (1997) Revision of the cerrado hemicryptophytic Chamaesyce of Boissier's &quot; Pleiadeniae &quot; (Euphorbiaceae). Brittonia 49: 155 - 180. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 2807678" type="journal article" year="1997">Simmons &amp; Hayden 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
